trans-unit.source: Represents a collection of <xref href="System.Security.Cryptography.X509Certificates.X509ChainElement"></xref> objects.
This class cannot be inherited.
An instance of this class is returned when the <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.X509Certificates.X509Chain.ChainElements%2A> property is called.
Copies an <xref href="System.Security.Cryptography.X509Certificates.X509ChainElementCollection"></xref> object into an array, starting at the specified index.
An array of <xref href="System.Security.Cryptography.X509Certificates.X509ChainElement"></xref> objects.
An integer representing the index value.
The specified index is less than zero, or greater than or equal to the length of the array.
array is `null`.
index plus the current count is greater than the length of the array.
Gets the number of elements in the collection.
Use this property to determine how many elements are in the collection.
An integer representing the number of elements in the collection.
Gets an <xref href="System.Security.Cryptography.X509Certificates.X509ChainElementEnumerator"></xref> object that can be used to navigate through a collection of chain elements.

The <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.X509Certificates.X509ChainElementEnumerator> class implements <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator>, which enables you to use methods such as <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.X509Certificates.X509ChainElementEnumerator.Current%2A>, <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.X509Certificates.X509ChainElementEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> and <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.X509Certificates.X509ChainElementEnumerator.Reset%2A> to view the contents of the collection.
An <xref href="System.Security.Cryptography.X509Certificates.X509ChainElementEnumerator"></xref> object.
Gets a value indicating whether the collection of chain elements is synchronized.
This value is always `false` because an <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.X509Certificates.X509ChainElementCollection> object is not thread safe.
Always returns `false`.
Gets the <xref href="System.Security.Cryptography.X509Certificates.X509ChainElement"></xref> object at the specified index.
Use this method to access an <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.X509Certificates.X509ChainElement> object in the collection.
An integer value.
An <xref href="System.Security.Cryptography.X509Certificates.X509ChainElement"></xref> object.
index is less than zero.
index is greater than or equal to the length of the collection.
Gets an object that can be used to synchronize access to an <xref href="System.Security.Cryptography.X509Certificates.X509ChainElementCollection"></xref> object.
This property returns the `this` pointer, which is a reference to an instance of the current class.
A pointer reference to the current object.
Copies an <xref href="System.Security.Cryptography.X509Certificates.X509ChainElementCollection"></xref> object into an array, starting at the specified index.
An array to copy the <xref href="System.Security.Cryptography.X509Certificates.X509ChainElementCollection"></xref> object to.
The index of array at which to start copying.
The specified index is less than zero, or greater than or equal to the length of the array.
array is `null`.
index plus the current count is greater than the length of the array.
Gets an <xref href="System.Collections.IEnumerator"></xref> object that can be used to navigate a collection of chain elements.
This method returns an enumerator interface.
An <xref href="System.Collections.IEnumerator"></xref> object.
